INSERT INTO `recipes` (id,category_id,name,intro,instruction,image,link,time,servings,calories,favorite) VALUES (1,1,'Perfect Sandwiches','Looking for the best sandwich recipe? Here you go!','Let''s melt 30 grams of butter in a frying pan on medium heat, add flour and cook for 1-2 minutes in a light roux. Pour the milk gradually and finally add 30 g Emmental cheese and cook 3-4 minutes, until the mixture gets thicker. Bechamel sauce is finished. Now spread half of bread with Dijon mustard, sprinkle with cheese and slices of ham. The remaining bread soak in cheese bechamel sauce and cover with them the bread with ham. After that spread butter on both sides of sandwiches and fry on a hot pan about 2-3 minutes on each side.','http://mock.robotemplates.com/cookbook/sandwiches.jpg','',20,4,160,0),
 (2,2,'Sausage Babies','These ever-popular sausage rolls are so easy to make and so delicious that you''ll never want the store-bought variety again.','Heat the oven to 200°C. Chop frankfurters roughly into thirds. Cut off several bands of puff pastry corresponding to the half size of sausages. Wrap frankfurters into strips of dough. Raddle with egg, sprinkle with sesame seeds and bake until pastry gets brown - it takes about 20-30 minutes.','http://mock.robotemplates.com/cookbook/sausage.jpg','',40,4,240,0),
 (3,3,'Goulash Soup','This hearty dish is popular in Austria and Hungary, and is great for lunch or dinner.','First of all we clean and peel the potatoes. Then we cut the potatoes on smaller pieces and put them into a stockpot which should be big enough. The potatoes should fill approximately one fifth of the pot. Then we add the peeled and sliced onions and the pot fill with water into the half. We shouldn''t forget to add a little bit of salt. Now we put the pot on the cooker. The cooking should take about half of hour and it''s good to blend the mixture regularly. When the water starts to boil we can add two cubes of bouillon and blend it again. Now we can add garlic sliced on small pieces and shredded sausage. In the meantime we can fire the pan with oil and admix the flour and red pepper very slowly. We originate some mash which we blend into the mixture in the big spot as soon as the potatoes are floppy enough. At the end we add the vegetables from the can, cream and little bit of marjoram spice. And now we have to taste it, of course! We should add more spices, salt or flour in the case that our Goulash is too thin. If everything is okay we can serve our delicious dish with fresh bread or rolls. Bon apetit!','assets://recipes/goulash.jpg','',60,6,80,0),
 (4,4,'Lángos','Lángos is Hungarian fried bread sometimes called Hungarian pizza. It is a favorite street and fair food.','We put warmish milk, a little spoon of sugar and a normal spoon of flour into a bowl, crumble the cube of yeast into it and let about 10 minutes leaven. Then we prepare another bowl and we mix flour, yoghurt, a pinch of salt and baking powder in it. We add the mixture from the first bowl, make a dough and immediately create Lángos which we fry on the hot pan with oil. When our Lángoses are done we smear them with ketchup mixed with mashed cloves of garlic. I recommend about 4 or 5 cloves but it depends how much do you like garlic and if you want to kiss somebody afterwards. At the end we grit our Lángos with grated cheese. And that''s all. Quite easy, isn''t it? Bon apetit!','http://mock.robotemplates.com/cookbook/langos.jpg','',45,4,430,0),
 (5,5,'Oven Roasted Potato Fries',NULL,'Preheat the oven to 200°C. In a large bowl, toss the potatoes with the oil and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Coat a baking sheet with cooking spray and spread the potatoes in a single layer. Bake until golden and crisp, about 30 minutes. Remove the fries with a spatula and season with salt.','http://mock.robotemplates.com/cookbook/fries.jpg','',45,4,190,0),
 (6,6,'Potato Wedges With Vegetable Salsa',NULL,'At first let''s boil potatoes cut into wedges. Meanwhile, prepare the vegetable salsa - dice the onion, tomatoes and eggplant into small pieces. Fry onion in a pan on a tablespoon of oil, add the tomatoes and eggplant and simmer together with a little balsamic vinegar for about 3-5 minutes to evaporate some of the liquid. Mix with the chopped herbs. Precooked potatoes put into baking pan, mix with 4 tablespoons of olive oil, salt, pepper and sprinkle with sesame seeds. Bake in oven preheated to 200°C for about 30-40 minutes. Serve with vegetable salsa.','http://mock.robotemplates.com/cookbook/vegetable.jpg','',60,2,40,0),
 (7,7,'Apple Pie','This is the best apple pie recipe for those who want an old-fashioned, perfect tasting apple pie with a flaky crust.','Mix sugar with eggs and melted butter. Add flour, baking powder and cinnamon. Mix thoroughly and then add to the dough roughly grated apples, raisins and nuts. Completely mixed dough pour into a greased baking mold and bake at 175°C for about 40 minutes, until cake gets golden brown color.','http://mock.robotemplates.com/cookbook/pie.jpg','',60,8,270,0),
 (8,8,'Orange Juice With Ginger','Orange juice recipes are simply the best! Try these combinations out and see what you think.','Let''s boil about 200 ml of water in a bigger pot. When the water starts boiling, put in a bag of tea and let it infuse for a while. Meanwhile, wash and peel the ginger and cut it into thin slices. Wash the oranges and cut them on slices as well. Add about 800 ml of orange juice and a few pieces of cloves to the tea in the pot and let''s boil it together. Then add the sliced ginger and 4 tablespoons of honey. Drink with slices of fresh orange.','http://mock.robotemplates.com/cookbook/juice.jpg','',20,5,50,0),
